        "title": "feat(agent-sdk): add packaging spec + skeleton",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds the Agent SDK Packaging spec (v0.2 draft) and implementation skeleton.\n\n## What's Included\n\n- `docs/specs/agent-sdk-packaging.md` — Full spec: manifest schema, integrity verification, secret scoping, network egress, mutable instruction policy, declarative upgrades, test harness, gateway config extension.\n- `packages/agent-sdk/` — TypeScript types, CLI stubs, test harness scaffold.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n- **openclaw.integrity.json** (not lockfile) — content integrity, not dependency resolution\n- **denyMutableInstructionFiles: true** — instruction files are prompt-layer code\n- **Config compiler dry-run in PR 3** — prove config shape before any live writes\n- **No scripts, no hooks** — purely declarative upgrades\n\n## PR Breakdown\n\nThis is a draft. Implementation planned across 9 incremental PRs:\n\n1. Schema + integrity manifest\n2. Secret scope + network policy types\n3. Config compiler dry-run\n4. Enable + disable\n5. Test harness\n6. Mutation detection + quarantine\n7. Config compiler live integration\n8. Declarative upgrade\n9. Documentation + examples\n\n## Status\n\nSpec review phase. Skeleton builds clean. No runtime changes yet.",
